default6. Concerns aboudefaultt body image issues in cdefaulthildrendefaultThis subject has see
defaultn much discussion in recent
default years. The overwhelming conclusion is that better education within families and by teachers is needed to mitigate the harmful effects of commercial fashion industry advertising and the concomitant peer pressure experienced by children. BN believes that a 
defaultproper understanding and acceptance of the human body from an early age provides the best background against which such education can be laid. To risk suppressing this kind of basic information from internet sources would not be helpful.
default&#xa0;
default7. defaultSafeguardingdefault edefaultducation in Art, Science, Medical health and Wdefaultellbeing, Sex and RelationshipsdefaultIt 
defaultmust be recognised that it 
defaultis 
defaulthow
default 
defaultbodies are
default shown that matters, not 
defaultwhat
default is shown
default. Legislation must take due account of the social and cultural value of material that happens
default to contains imagery of naked humans. None of the areas listed here is trivial; all may have to refer to the human body as it actually is. Despite the r
defaulteservations 
defaultof some minorities
default, the right to publish and consume such important material is of paramount
default significanc
defaulte to every new generation in our culture and country.
default&#xa0;
default8. ConclusiondefaultIn summary, we look to parenting and education to inform children of the risks inherent in internet use, to established authorities to block illegal content, and to society in
default general to continue to broaden its tolerance of harmless and potentially valuable 
defaultattitudes
default. [4]
